	Excellent for short stop over in Dubai	We were flying to Cape Town from Birmingham but Emirates decided the transfer times were too tight between the flights and offered us a stopover in Dubai. Originally this was to be for only 7 hours but I negotiated a 24 hours stop over with them. The hotel is literally 5 mins from the airport. A driver collected us and we were taken to the hotel which had a separate Emirates' reception. The booking in procedure was very smooth and we were in our rooms and resting very quickly. The rooms were fine, very much as expected with good facilities although the bathroom was particularly small for a hotel of this grade. We used the buffet restaurant for lunch and it had a very good selection of cuisines from around the world. The service was very attentive. We had our evening meal at the hotel's Italian restaurant and found that a little disappointing. There was a huge range of dining options and I am sure something for everyone.We took the hotel's shuttle bus into the city at 1700 hrs and this was rush hour so it took almost an hour. We wandered around the souks and then caught a taxi back for only 20 DHR - much quicker once the traffic had eased.All in all, a good quality hotel that you would expect from the Meridien group. Perfect for airport connections, a bit far out for the city and the beach.	
	Started as Hell but ended as Heaven	A real mix of a holiday - started off as hell but ended as heavenAfter a very long day and flight on arrival at the hotel we were shown straight to our room, where we were checked in, (very nice touch) and was immediately made to feel very welcome. The next day after breakfast we noticed that there were workmen outside our room building a new swimming pool. Did not think this would be a problem as we only sleep in room! But no, the workmen continued working all through the night with drills, hammer guns and electric saws. Foolishly we thought they must be finishing off as no one would work through the night at a hotel like this - disturbing the guests....Wrong. After two nights of this, we spoke to reception who said to pack up and we would be moved later in the day to another room. But by 4.00pm we were still waiting, and when questioned reception about our move we was told that our room move was now not going to happen...... We requested to see the manager and explained to him the situation. I was now at the &quot;tears&quot; stage, no sleep for two nights, and it was becoming a nightmare holiday...The Duty Manager (Anthony) was an absolute saint. He could not have been more helpful, accommodating and apologetic and a new room was found for us. He also arranged for our bags to be taken immediately and later a bottle of wine to be sent to our room as an apology. The new room was an upgrade on what we had originally book and was wonderful, and more than made up for the noise in the last one. And as we were now able to get a good nights sleep we were able to appreciate the other good points of the hotel such as the village restaurants etc. By the end of our break away I can say with all honesty it was one of the best holidays I have ever had in Dubai. I would recommend this hotel to anyone, and would be more than happy to return again, and finally a big thank you to Anthony.	
