Aug 15 2009 	High Service Level Out dated Rooms but Good Value for Money	The Le Meridien Dubai is the Airport Hotel. It's located very near to Dubai Airport. It runs a shuttle service to Terminal 1. It's well suited for a stop over. I've stayed three nights in a Classic Room. The hotel is 5 star but the Classic Room is not. It's outdated, especially the bathroom which is more 3-star. But even the Classic Room is equipped with a flat screen TV with a DVD player.There are over 15 restaurants and bars. The room service menu is seperate from the restaurant menus. The room service food is good but not exeptional. The food presentation is. Breakfast is a bit expensive at AED 109 but very good with lots to choose from including many fresh juices, cheeses and even smoked salmon. The presentation of the food is once again very beautiful.The two pools are a bit dissapointing. They offer almost no shadow and are too deep to be used by young children.As with most 5 star hotels is about the service level which is very good. A free newspaper or complementary ice bucket is brought to your room straight away after one phone call. Staff (mostly asian) is very polite. On check out the bill showed lots of mini bar items I didn't consume but the manager took immediate care of that.There is a supermarket located outside the hotel but I didn't go there because of the scorcing heat. Better to take a short taxi ride to a mall and shop there. Wired internet is expensive at AED 1 per minute with a minimum of 15 minutes.The Le Meridien offers great value for money at the moment at rates (without breaffast) that start at as little as AED 280 (around 60 Euro). Any rate up to AED 400 is OK. Above that I think that the rooms need an renovation first.	
Aug 11 2009 	ABSOLUTELY FANTASTIC! TOP CLASS HOTEL	We have just come back from a wonderful holiday at Le Meridien in Dubai and thought the hotel and the facilities superb.On arrival in Dubai we were disappointed that the free shuttle bus was no longer available but transport could be organised at 50 dhs. Having lived in Dubai we knew exactly where the hotel was and jumped in a taxi and within 2 minutes were there which was fantastic.Our flight got in early in the morning and we knew we were too early to check in but went to the hotel nevertheless, after waiting for an hour and a half we were taken to our room. The staff were very courteous and the receptionist showed us to our room and informed us that we had been upgraded to an &quot;art and tech&quot; room.The room was extremely clean, spacious and modern. I would have no complaints what so ever about the cleanliness or housekeeping staff, they really were fantastic.In our room we had a luxurious bathroom complete with power shower and bath. Some people on trip advisor critisised the size of the bathrooms but we found it more than adequate. The room was very modern and had lots of storage, a desk, fridge, mini bar, dvd player, plasma screen, tea/coffee machine, touch screen controls for lights and air con etc. The room was simply perfect, I could have stayed there longer.With this room you get fresh fruit delivered to your room in the evening which was a nice touch and most appreciated.The only problem we had in the two weeks we were there was our remote control batteries went for the television. This didn't pose a problem however, after phoning housekeeping someone arrived and fitted the batteries within 5 mins - hows that for service?We hadn't planned on spending so much time by the poolside but the pool was so inviting and yet again the pool area were well presented and clean. The poolside staff were very friendly and helpful, they really did look after us.We ate most days at the poolside bar and were never disappointed. We also ate in the Yalumba restaurant a few nights and were very impressed with their special offer (99 dishes for 99dhs), real value for money and everything was so tasty.We were really happy with the location of the hotel for what we had planned to do in Dubai, I think it is very well located. There is a courtesy bus to Deira City Centre Mall and we had a courtesy bus to take us to the airport when we checked out. The rest of the time we used the readily available taxis outside the hotel which were cheap enough.If you are thinking of booking this hotel for a holiday or business trip I would highly recommend it. It is without doubt the best hotel I have ever stayed in and will look forward to visiting again in the not to distant future. I guarantee you will not be disappointed.	
