Jan 24 2009	There are Much Better Places to Stay in Dubai	We stayed at Le Meridian-Dubai for 2 nights a the end of a 6 week tour of Australia/New Zealand.We had paid extra for a Club Room after having had a fantastic stay in a club room at the Grosvenor 18 months ago.The Le Meridian was extremely disappointing and the extra paid for the club room was a total waste of money. The room was very dated with poor decoration. The bathroom was also poor without any of the 5star luxury that we had seen at the Grosvenor.The evening canapes and cocktails that are part of the Club experience were a farce. House wine and a single (poor) canape. None of the champagne and fine wines with delicious hot selection of canapes that we were expecting.If you are looking for a room to catch an early flight,at the nearby airport ,and can secure a low price, it may be OK. If you are looking for somewhere with a taste of luxury, forget it !!!	
Jan 5 2009 	Not a five-star experience	There are many other, better five-stars in Dubai for the same amount of money. The room was fine (unlike other reviewers, I was not upgraded). I appreciated the in-room espresso machine, but the bathroom was extremely dated -- a cheap wall-mounted hair dryer and flimsy shower curtain don't meet my definition of luxury. The gym closed at 10 pm -- in fact, the one of the gym workers unplugged my treadmill while I was still running on it at 9:50 -- so the facilities are not available for those travelers who might arrive late at night and want to work out. The room service menu was surprisingly limited for a hotel that boasts 17 restaurants, and had very few healthy vegetarian options such as salads. The internet costs extra. The staff seemed friendly and helpful.	
Jan 4 2009 	Le Meridien is pretty nice (45 stars)	Nice big scale luxury hotel with some issues. Firstly the location is remote: it takes more than 20 minutes to get to Jumeirah Beach, so if you value sea, pick a hotel closer to the Dubai Marina or Jumeirah (and most likely pay more for that). Otherwise it doesn't matter since Dubai as a city is like Los Angeles: you need to take a taxi to get anywhere anyways. Thankfully it's rather cheap.Secondly the pool areas are inadequate. The three pools are able to barely accommodate guests and there seems to be a culture of reserving chairs early in the morning with a book, towel etc. but not using them. So the best seats are taken through the day, but most remain empty. Common in three star family hotels and not very luxurious.Third problem was the concierge service which is a must in a city as sprawled as Dubai. Though staff was rather helpful and polite, it was reactive, never proactive. Dry alcohol-free nights (which occurred 2 times in 7 days) and such were not communicated to guests if not specifically asked.Le Meridien is a nice hotel especially for families. Staff is mostly very professional, restaurants serve quality food and the ambiance is sophisticated. If you aren't looking for a boutique experience, but a luxurious resort kind of hotel, Le Meridien is a good pick.	
Jan 3 2009 	Amazing Experience!	We arrived at the hotel and as we had a courtesy shuttle included with our stay, we approached the hotel desk and after a short way were whisked away to a shuttle and literally two minutes later arrived at the hotel! The front desk staff were extremely kind and as we were too early to be able to get into our room we were provided with full access to the fitness centre to shower and change into fresh clothes - this was great! We did just that and then headed straight into town. The hotel provides free shuttle service to the Dubai Mall and to Deira City Centre Mall - or if you prefer, it will get you a hotel taxi (a luxury lexus or merc) or a local taxi.The breakfast is absolutely exquisite with fresh eggs, pancakes, dosas, made to order - just the way you like it! The restaurants in the hotel also provide a delicious array of food.The staff are extremely polite and friendly and will try and do their best to please you.This hotel is a definite must stay! Especially if you enjoy being pampered and looked after!	
