Dec 6 2008 	Food lovers delight	We stayed here for five days before continuing to Mauritius so our purpose was discovering Dubai rather than enjoying the beaches. To this end it was a perfect choice. Located near the airport (although you never heard the planes) and allowing easy access to Deira and Bur Dubai it is a good location if the focus of your trip is the city itself. Perhaps because of this it is predominantly a business travellers hotel. In a city where newer, bigger, better is constantly being developed keeping up with the crowd is the ongoing challenge and Le Meridien's claim to food is its gastronomie. There are no less than 15 different restaurants offering all types of cuisine from French to Australian and Lebanese to Thai. Some of these are in an annex attached to the hotel whilst others are scattered around an attractive courtyard where al fresco dining is the way to go. Note however that non are particularly cheap but there are deals and special offers at certain times. Best of all however is the breakfast which is a veritable feast of well prepared fresh food, fruits and pastries.The level of service in the hotel couldn't be faulted. As other reviewers have mentioned if you arrive early as we did you are likely to have to wait for your room but they endeavoured to prepare our room as soon as possible (we still had a few hours wait) and did provide free drinks at the lobby bar whilst we waited. The hotel is beautifully decorated and we had no complaints about our room. I'd read that some of the rooms are a bit shabby but unless ours had been recently renovated this certainly wasn't the case. We had a problem once with the coffee machine so I called and literally within a minute someone came and fixed it. The facilities are good. There are two smallish leisure pools and a pool for lane swimming. The gym is very good but we never used the spa (no time).It is easy to get taxis (walking anywhere isn't really an option) and there is a courtesy bus to the city centre mall which is not as high profile as some of the newer malls but is just as good. If you want to spend more time in 'modern Dubai' then you should probably stay in Jumeirah or Sheik Zayed Rd as the journey can be quite lenghty and a bit pricey but if it is the Creek, the souks and old Dubai that you are after then it is a great base.All in all we were more than satisfied with Le Meridien.	
