Apr 16 2008 	Great for a stopover	Decided to stay at this hotel as only had 1 night in Dubai and friends had advised to stay near the airport as traffic can get congested in Dubai. We landed in Dubai at 6am following a 6 hour night time flight from Bangkok and waited approx 10 mins for transfer bus - could probably have walked from airport as very close. We had to wait until 10am for our room, but check in should have been 2pm, so couldn't complain. We had an express continental breakfast from the coffee/snack bar in the hotel foyer for about £6 - good value. The staff are very polite and for our stay provided a 5 star service. Our room was lovely considering we had gone for the most basic and had everything we needed. The 3 pools are clean and the lifeguards lay your towels out if the pool is not too busy with swimmers. We ate in the Italian restaurant in the Meridian Village and had a drink in the Dubliner. Both enjoyable, if not a little expensive, but then you are in a 5 star hotel, so will be expected to pay 5 star prices. Our package did not include breakfast so ended up paying £15 each, however there was a great selection to choose from. There was hardly any noise from the airport. However, due to the hotels location by the airport it is a taxi ride to any other places in Dubai - Jumeirah Beach is 25 mins and the creek 15 mins if you don't get stuck in traffic as we did. It is actually nice to walk along the creek. Overall - great hotel, but a taxi ride to the tourist spots. Taxis are reasonable though.	
