Apr 17 2007	Couldn't recommend it highly enough!	I have just got back from a 5 night stay at the Meridien Dubai with my sister and it was absolutely fantastic!! We booked a Royal Club room after comments from the site and it was definitely worth paying the extra for. This includes a very smart private limousine pick up to and from the airport. Although we arrived very early (8am ish) they showed us straight through to the lounge for breakfast and made sure our room was ready by th time we'd finished. The room was lovely and looked out over the tennis courts. The Royal Club rooms are on the ground floor and some overlook the pools and garden area. Each day we had a platter of fresh fruit left in our room. Later in the day there would be a savoury and a sweet canape and an apperitif. The rooms are very clean and generally well sound proofed - with great black out curtains for that afternoon sleep! The staff were all so friendly and helpful. They work extremely hard! They did over and above what was expected. We asked for directions to the next door hotel, the doorman noticed my sister had hurt her foot and actually drove us round there - for no extra cost! It was a really nice touch. The hotels faciliaties were fantastic. Three pools, each quite different. A great gym. And a Health Spa. The treatments in the spa are extra but the gym and the classes there are free. They offer free transers to the Gold souk and their two beach hotels - but you do have to pay for a day pass if you want to go to these. The hotel had a good choice of restaurants, althoughthe atmosphere is livlier on Thursdays and Fridays (their weekend). Sunday and Monday, before we left were very quiet! The Royal Club price includes use of the separate business lounge. So you can use that for free - good for checking up on your emails! The Royal club lounge includes a great breakfast - freshly cooked pancakes, eggs, whichever way you like them, the normal range of cooked breakfast and a selection of pastries and savouries. Tea, coffee and soft drinks are free in there all day. Little sandwiches are served between 3 - 6pm. Alcohol is free after 6pm and canapes are served between 7pm and 8pm. They orgainised a late check out for us to 4pm. So we really felt as though we'd got an extra day. We could use the faciliaties from 8am on the day we arrived, right until we got our lift to th airport at 11pm last night. All for no extra charge! oh yes - it is very close to the airport...2 minutes drive - but amazingly there is no disturbance at all from the airport. We didn't hear any planes the whole time we were there, even when lying by the pool. I can recommend this for a luxury break, for families, couples and friends. Well worth the money!	
