Jan 5 2007 	Good hotel good service great breakfast	The hotel is near the airport but surprising we haven't heard any noise during our stay. It's a little far from the beach and the old city but only marginally. When I saw the other hotels around town, they are all spread out and you need to hail a taxi anyway. Our taxi trips to almost anywhere is around AED40 which is just US10.The service in this hotel is very good. In fact it's great when you compared with other hotels and places we visited in Dubai. I say that with reservations may be because I am from Hong Kong and service in Asia in general is just a notch above this part of the world. It's just different culture. I guess the erractic service is inevitable because the people who work in hotels, taxis and restaurants are not local arabs but people from South Asian and Eastern Europe etc, and they probably don't enjoy their lives much in Dubai except to work there. So everyone doesn't seem to be enjoying themselves very much.Do try to avoid the old rooms and book the refurbished rooms. The hotel is very 1980s so is the pool but well maintained. The art and tech room we stayed in is very nice though with a serene view of the lawn and pool. The breakfast is the best I have ever had.Overall I love my experience in the le meridien.	
