Oct 17 2006 	Gay Travellers take care!	We were booked into this hotel by Emirates, and arrived after a long, long direct flight from Melbourne.When we checked in, feeling fairly exhausted, the staff were astonished to find before them two men wishing to sleep in the same bed.They couldn't fathom it out. After much to-ing and fro-ing they managed to find us a twin room - with two huge beds in, which suited us just fine. Still, the wait while this was sorted was that last thing we needed after the flight.But if you're two men travelling together, it's probably a good idea to let them know in advance - or be sure to book a twin room - so there's no problems at check in.Otherwise, we loved the hotel: great gym, good breakfast, lovely pools. Sure the bathrooms are not brilliant, but the beds were so comfortable and I never heard a plane the whole time I was there.	
