Aug 3 2006 	Most welcoming	I have stayed at this hotel dozens of times over the last 3 years whilst travelling through on business. From the moment you arrive at the Meridian desk at the airport you are taken care of and are made very welcome. The check in is fast and you never need worry about baggage as that is looked after from airport to room. the staff are always polite and genuinely welcoming, particularly if you are a frequent guest. The rooms are a good size with really comfortable huge beds,Plasma tv, dvd, minibar etc although it would be wise to buy duty free if you wish to avoid mini bar prices. The lobby bar has a nice atmosphere with a resident pianist and singer and there are numerous restaurants whithin, that cater for all tastes and pockets. Sure the drinks can be a bit pricey but this is a 5 star hotel and you get what you pay for. The Meridian village at the rear of the hotel has a a nice setting with more restaurants and an Irish Bar, big screen Tv, live sport, good food and well patronised by expats. The open air terrace restaurant is great value with a marvellous buffet and live music. The Pool areas are first class and never too busy and there is an excellant gym if you feel energetic. The hotel is well placed for the airport, golf, tennis and city centre all of which are only a short , cheap taxi drive away ( nobody walks in Dubai, it's usually far too hot).All in all an excellant hotel that would suit business travellers or couples. Families with children would find other hotels in the Jumeriah beach area more suitable. The Meridian is a well run, relaxing hotel that I would have no hesitation in recommending and one that would put to shame many uk and european hotels of the same category.	
Jul 28 2006 	Amazing food close to airport	This trip was the first time I went to Dubai, and I wasn’t quite sure what to expect, so I decided to spend my time in two hotels instead on one.I was travelling with my little sister who is 15, so I wanted to stay somewhere that would have a lot of things do, and be of a high standard.Because of the great reviews seen on trip advisor, and the inclusion of a water park in the hotel, I decided the Jumeirah Beach Hotel would be a great place to experience the beach side of Dubai, whist I chose The Le Meriden Dubai as my second hotel because of its closeness to the airport, and city centre.The Le Meriden Dubai isn’t as new as some of the hotels in Jumeirah say, so some of the decor may look a bit warn, however they were doing maintenance repairs while we were there so things are getting better.The Deluxe room was slightly above average because of the inclusion of a plasma screen TV, DVD player and mini bar, but the bathroom and everything else was quite average.The swimming pools were nice, with the inclusion of a pool side bar that can make you delicious milkshakes and fruit juices, and lots of deck chairs and towels to chill out.The best thing about this hotel though was the food! So much many restraints of a high standard, if you’re a food lover this is a great place to stay or at least visit while in Dubai.We ate at the Lebanese Restaurant which provided a great entertainment with belly dancing any live music; however I wasn’t too keen on the food because it contained a lot of pickle dishes for the starter.The Thai restaurant has excellent food though, with fresh giant shrimp, lobster and delicious Thai curries!Room service was great too, and quite reasonably prices, a meal for 2 came to approx 150Dhs.The proximity of the hotel to the airport is a huge bonus surprisingly, as you would expect this to be a negative because of the noise. But the planes must be flying the other direction or something, because we could hear nothing! The hotel provides regular shuttle buses to the airport, which takes only 15 minutes, which was great because Dubai's traffic can make travel times unpredictable at times.In summary, The Le Meriden Dubai is a nice hotel, with great food, and average rooms, within good distance from the airport. But if your coming to Dubai for a family holiday, I would definitely recommend Jumeirah Beach, as there are much more things to do for kids.	
