May 5 2006	Great hotel	This Meridien was a great choice now that I have seen Dubai. It is on the Deira side of the city. Bur Dubai and Jumeirah area are on the other side. The building work in Bur Dubai and Jumeirah is so extensive at the moment and probably will be for another few years. I would not recommend staying in Bur Dubai or Jumeriah beach area. You have all the nice hotels on one side of the road and miles of building work in front of them. The Meridien was only a few minutes from the airport. They provide free transportation to and from the airport at all times. The have a courtesy bus that leaves on the hour each day that leaves you into Deira Shopping Centre and will bring you back again. A taxi is only approx €2.50 each way. I had a concern being near the airport would I hear planes all of the time. Absolutely no way. I never heard any. It is a two storey hotel but the facilities are great. It has three pools, with sun loungers, shades and they provide towels. 15 restaurants, dont be fooled in the Bistro, if you think the champagne is complimentary when you arrive. It is nearly €45.00 for the two glasses. You can say no of course. The bedrooms are large and the bathrooms are okay. The staff were very good and helpful. Overall I dont feel it was a plush five star but it is definitetly higher than a four star. If I ever return to Dubai, I would stay here and would recommend it to anyone. I decided to stay in a Meridien so as I could use the facilities of the Meridien's on Jumeriah Beach if I wanted to but no thanks. The traffic in Dubai is terrible and can last from 4pm until 10pm daily. We avoided this with staying at the Le Meridien.	
May 3 2006 	Our favourite	My husband and I travel through Dubai regularly. Over the years we have stayed in many hotels in Dubai. The standard of hotels in Dubai is very high, but Le Meridien holds its own very well, even though it is an older hotel. Some of the positives for me are the excellent service, the ammenities, the location and the layout of the hotel. Although the hotel is right by the airport, the hotel has free shuttle buses to most of the major attractions. This was something that I haven't found at any of the other hotels. So even though you are conveniently located near the airport you are not inconvenienced by being away from the centre of town.The same can be said of the restaurants. You are away from the restaurant centres near the beach and in Bur Dubai, but it is not a problem because the hotel has some of the most popular restaurants in Dubai, so you will find that many people come to Le Meridien for the great variety and calliber of resturants.The health club is also well known to residents of Dubai and is very popular with good reason, it is one of the best health clubs I have ever been to. The hotel is a 2 storey building that is spread around three pools, which makes it feel more like a holiday resort than a lot of the other high-rise hotels. This is a huge bonus for us as business travellers who would like to unwind, but only have a day or two in transit to do so. The atmosphere at Le Meridien relaxes you immediately.The rooms are very comfortable and clean as you expect. I would recommend it over any other hotel in Dubai.	
