May 2 2006	Second visit to Le meridien	Stayed at Hotel for 4 nights end of April after attending conference at another hotel in Dubai. Had previously stayed at Le Meridien two years ago and specifically chose it again for a few days relaxing after conference. Had read reviews before trip so a bit concerned at some of the criticisms.But overall having stayed at Hotel, would have to say it is excellent for guests not wanting a beach experience. It is principally a business hotel so very few children and guests are asked not to dress in shorts and sun tops for breakfast. But this business feel certainly is far more appealing than the busyness and holiday dress of the beach hotels. It is really a matter of choice.THe hotel now has a third pool in the inner courtyard, reserved solely for guests at the hotel and we found it to be a haven of quietness, unlike the main pool area which we found quite noisy - constant music from the bar and used by a lot of health club members. The courtyard pool had no music. Service around the pool just fantastic with cold towels brought round and the lunch we ordered brought to our sunbeds on trays laid most beautifully with linen cloth and napkins and flowers. Fantastic value for money too in exquisitely presented food. The courtyard pool closes at 6pm. At the back of the health club is the fitness pool - just marvellous for an early morning swim as it opens at 6.30am.Breakfast at the Yalumba restaurant is extraordinarily good value - excellent juices, fruit, yogurts and wide selection of different cold and hot dishes. Service from the staff could not be faulted here. Dinner in this Australian themed restaurant is also excellent.Situation of the hotel is excellent- it is close to airport but aircraft noise is not intrusive. You get some take off noise. But for ease of travel into the centre of the city it is very good and given that the roads in Dubai are now just at a standstill at some times with the excessive number of cars, it is much quicker to travel from the Meridien than from the beach hotels. It could easily take an hour now to go from Beach hotels to airport at peak times.The criticisms I would make are:1. We arrived at the hotel at around 12.30pm as we were moving from our first hotel. However, the reception staff would not make our room available until 2pm, the official check in time. This seemed somewhat unhelpful. We had booked via the Meridien website and chosen the superior room package ( the cheapest option )- the others being the de luxe rooms and the Club rooms).2. With hindsight we should have paid the extra money for, preferably, a Club room. The superior rooms, being the lowest priced, look out over the car parking areas. The hotel was built quite a number of years ago, when hotel bathrooms were much smaller than recently built hotels so the bathrooms of these superior rooms present as very basic indeed - very small and cramped with very dated decoration and showing signs of wear- not to a five star standard at all. Absolutely pristine in cleanliness though and ample towel changes. We too only had one robe and slippers on arrival but requested another set - think one only suppled as this is mainly a business hotel so probably usually only have one person occupancy. But for a five star hotel you would expect housekeeping to check on the number of guests. Bed size too needs consideration as the superior and de luxe rooms only have a queen size bed - 5'6&quot; width where you would usually expect a king - 6'0&quot; bed in a 5 star hotel even in the basically priced rooms. These superior rooms echo more of the standard of a US Holiday Inn - which I would never class as a 5 star hotel.3. Because it is a business hotel and near to airport, there is corridor noise and plumbing noise both late at night and early morning. We adapted to this but if you are a light sleeper you would need ear plugs.But for all these criticisms, I would certainly stay here again - the grounds and pools are fantastic and the staff exceptionally attentive and polite. Food and service are first rate. And with a Club room you should have an excellent bedroom as well.	
