Apr 4 2006	We hope to return back again	We just came back from Dubai in which we celebrated our twenty five yearswedding anniversary. We spent five days in Le Meridien Airport. It is a fantastichotel.We were treated like royalty. The staff are excellent, they all courteous,polite,truly fantastic! The service cannot be faulted. The location was ideal because it is not in the middle of the hustle andbustle of construction developments.Our six year old son loved it. The three swimming pools in the hotel areexcellent and not crowded. It doesn?t matter what time you turn up to swim,you will always find beds. The pool attendants are always ready to sort yourbeds and they will bring you cooltowels to refresh you. If you like the beach, the hotels courtesy mini buswill pick you up at 10.30 to drop you at the sister hotels Le Meridien Beachor Mina Seyahi (choice is yours) and will collect you at 1630 to take youback. However make sure you book it. Also the hotel has another courtesybus to take you to the gold and spice markets every morning at 09.45. Otherthan that there is an hourly shuttle service to take you to the city shoppingcentre. Finally every half an hour there is a courtesy bus to the airportto dropyou or pick you up. It is all free.The hotel rooms are big which include silk bed linens and feather pillows,a large plasmatelevision, and complimentary slippers and dressing gowns. Also every morningthere is fresh fruit and free bottles of water on your table.The bath rooms are not big but very clean and always topped up with Molton&amp;Brown shampoo, and body lotions.There are at least five different restaurants on site. Each one of them doingdifferent nightly promotions. For around £25.00 you can eat and drink ata restaurant.(Our six years old boy wasn?t charged).We also attended a dessert safari and Arabian barbecue, which was truly amazing.I recommend it highly. The safari starts with driving through the dessertin a 4X4(dune bashing). We then visited a camel farm campsite for barbecue,went on a camel ride and enjoyed the sand boarding. All in all it is a excellenthotel. We hope to return back again. I would confidentially recommend itto anyone.	
Mar 28 2006	Great Customer Service	We stayed at this hotel from 15th to 18th March. We were impressed by the facilities offered by the Royal Club package and would probably use the hotel again.We used the pools and other facilities early morning and thus avoided any of the congestion that can occurr.The Meridien Village was an enjoyable (though sometimes expensive)dining experience (best value by far was the Irish Bar - Dubliners).One major area of concern was the effectiveness of reception staff in the business suite of Royal Club. I asked for two items of very important mail to be sent to the UK whilst we were there. To date, some 2 weeks later neither has arrived!On the whole a positive and welcoming experience but not one to entrust for any critical business tasks!	
Mar 26 2006	Very happy	I read most of the reviews before I went to get a feel for what to expect. We could not fault the place - especially the staff. We arrived very early in the morning (off a 15 hours flight) not expecting a room to be ready - but the staff went out of their way to get one for us quickly - offering us a free breakfast while we waited and then sending a bottle of wine to our room as a gift for waiting patiently.Reading some of the other reviews we wondered if we'd be able to make use of the sister hotel for free (as we had a very cheap deal with Emirates). Apparently that's all to do with your travel agent so perhaps check before you go and you won't be disappointed (Trailfinders in Aust, UK and Ireland offer this to customers).We'd stay there again, it was great!	
Mar 19 2006	Not up to scratch	I have just returned from a business trip to Dubai staying at the Meridien, conveniently situated by the airport. This is a five star hotel with a few problems. I had booked on line via Expedia and on arrival was disappointed with the room, in particular the bathroom which was ridiculously small, dark and in desperate need of refurbishment. One would expect aircraft noise at this hotel and it causes a minor irritation during the day but every night I was woken periodically by the bigger jets taking off. This should definitely be taken into consideration by light sleepers. The hotel is large and impersonal with indifferent staff manning the reception, restaurants and bars, the domestics and pool attendants are courteous. The clerk on the car hire desk was cold and unfriendly on both occasions we had cause to interact with her. An altogether more serious problem was the drunkeness of some of the guests (mostly English I am afraid) around the pool areas at all hours of the day. Middle aged men and women staggered around from early morning to late evening shouting and using the most disgusting language I have ever heard with total disregard for the embarrassment of other guests including small children. The staff were seemingly unable or unwilling to intervene, men in suits periodically appeared to survey the sorry scene then retreated back behind their desks. There are not enough sun beds provided around the three pools resulting in the usual hogging of the loungers by guests who fail to appear to use them. The Meridien Village has a selection of restaurants and bars which cater for almost every taste, Tex Mex and the Irish Bar are the most popular and are good value for money, I recommend the latter in particular if you are English and in need of something familiar. I had booked on a room only basis and discovered on the last morning of my stay that you can get a very good breakfast in the foyer cafe for roughly half the price of the overpriced meal in the Yalumba breakfast restaurant. I would not recommend this hotel and will definitely avoid it in the future.	
Mar 9 2006	We loved it	We stayed at Le Meridien and could not fault the hotel. The staff were very attentive,polite and friendly, the hotel spotlessly clean. Location to us was perfect - not in the middle of the mass of construction. My 7 year old daughter loved the 3 pools at the hotel &amp; they fully compensated for no sea!We could have spent a week at the hotel and never left the doorstep. The health &amp; beauty facilites on site were excellent and again the staff very friendly. There are ample of places to eat, offering a range of types of food. The Terrace resturant is a must - booking recommended. I can not rate the place enough &amp; can't wait to go back.	
Feb 2 2006	Fab Hotel	I have just returned from a five night stay in Dubai, and would definately recommend the Le Meridien Dubai, despite being literally 2 min taxi ride from the airport, the hotel is nothing like an airport hotel. It has 14 restaurants, an irish bar, and a club/bar with live music. Also two pools (and they are planning another one), and the main pool has a swim up bar. (lovely!)One of the hotels biggest assets, has to be the staff, who go out of their way to help without a second thought, and unlike a lot of american hotel staff they don't hang around waiting for a tip.The hotel is about 10 mins taxi ride to the main areas of Bur Dubai, Jemeriah and Deria, but taxis are so cheap (15-30 Dhs approx £2-£5) that it didn't matter.We booked an excursion through the hotel to spend the morning Sand Dunning, Camel Riding and Sand Boarding, and despite having to get up at 8am (with a hang over) It was fantastic, I particularily enjoyed the Sand Boarding, which is surprisingly easier than it looks. It was excellent value for money, and so easy to book.	
Jan 18 2006	Romantic Country	For my 21 anniversary my husband booked us into Le Meridien Dubai, as a surprise. We stayed for 4 nights. I am well travelled, and I can safely recommend this Hotel. We were treated excellently by all staff members who ensured our comfort transport to and from the Airport only 3 minutes away. At night the hotel provided live music in the huge marbel lounge with a wide choice of various music sounds and eating establishments wrapped around the Hotel. At night water fountains ran throughout the complex with soft coloured lighting all adding to the atmosphere. Culture and the design of buildings took my breath away. I would fully recommend a visit to this beautiful country and hotel. I cannot wait for my return visit.	
Dec 19 2005	Ideal for airport and city	Literally 3 minutes from the airport, Le Meridian was a perfect basis for our 5 day city break.Room was large and very clean, no compliants there ! Staff were very friendly, breakfasts were very nice also. The hotel has approx. 10 restaurants and every meal we had was excellent (but book early). The hotel's gym is very large and spacious, and the treadmills have individual screens to watch tv whilst running. The pool areas (2) are well maintained and the pool was lovely and warm.The City Mall is close by (5-10 minute taxi ride) which has a good selection of shops. Al Karama is a shopping area for &quot;replica&quot; watches and handbags but you will be harassed (as we were in the Gold Souk). We took the complimentary bus to their sister hotel on the beach (a long 45 minute bus ride). There is a huge amount of buidling work going on and we wished we'd stayed put - oh well. Overall, this hotel was excellent and will definetly return.	
Nov 15 2005	Alright except for the bathroom	My family stayed for 5 nights at this hotel. We had complimentary hotel pickup from the airport and check-in was very fast. The decor was what you would expect of a 5* hotel. My gripe was with the bathroom. We took a deluxe room and the bathroom was tiny, the tub was stained and the shower curtain smelled. The shower mixer was loosely hanging off the wall and the we would be in ankle deep water before the water started to drain. The bathroom fittings looked old and didn't fit in with the 5* decor of the room. Having said that, both bathroom and room were spotlessly clean and towels were changed daily. I was a little disappointed that our room did not have complimentary coffee/tea making facilities, we had to borrow a kettle to make milk for our young child. The tv stations were quite bad and they didn't have any good movie channels, not even HBO. The room service menu was very limited. The bathroom however had Hermes shower products which was a nice touch.The breakfast buffet was varied but it never changed during the 6 days we were there. We kind of got tired of it by the 4th day. There is however an 'egg station' which you can order your eggs from the waiter and it would be served at your table. Toast and a few selection of muffins and breads were also available.We had access to Le Meridien's sister hotel at Jumeirah Beach which we thoroughly enjoyed. The free transport leaves at 10.30am and the journey takes roughly about half an hour in non-peak traffic. Beach towels are given in exchange for your passport/driving license or any other type of identificaton so remember to bring one along. We had access to the terrific pool and beautiful beach. There were clean shower stalls, toilet and changing area with lockers at the beach resort and you could shower off before you caught the transport back to Dubai at 4.30pm, Molton Brown products were given which I thought was a nice touch. A word of advice though - book early if you want to visit the beach as Le Meridien Dubai only gives out 15 passes a day. The hotel also had daily free transport to the Gold Souk and City Centre which is a huge shopping centre. We visited City Centre daily for our meals as they had 2 foodcourts - 1 slightly cheaper and 1 slightly upmarket. Macdonalds, Burger King and KFC were located at the cheaper foodcourt and if you have kids there is something like a kiddyland with rides and merry-go-round which they would love. There was also a Carrefour which was convenient as we would buy food there and take it back to our hotel to eat as we were there during Ramadan and the foodcourt was closed.The complimentary transport fetches you there but there is no pick-up back to the hotel so you have to catch a cab back. It's about a 10 minute taxi ride and would cost you something like 10 dirhams.Despite the hotel's close proximity to the airport, not once did we hear any planes taking off nor was it ever noisy, it was quiet at night and we all slept well.Complimentary transfer to the airport leaves every half-hour but be sure to inform the reception staff what time you want to catch the transfer. Despite the hotel's strict policy that check-out is at 12noon, we managed to get late check out at 3.30pm as our flight was at 6pm, I thought they were rather accommodating.Despite my gripe about the bathroom, I would highly recommend this hotel for friendly staff, proximity to the airport, shopping centre and cleanliness.	
