Nov 1 2005	Best Value Dubai City and Beach	The Meridien Dubai City hotel is 3 km from the airport - but don't let that put you off. It is quiet, in fact, it is more peaceful than the beach locations, which suffer construction 24 hours a day.We have not stopped congratulating ourselves on our decision to stay in the city centre, which afforded us all the luxury of a beach side hotel, a choice of two swimming pools and 10 restaurants with easy access to City centre attractions all at a third of the price of staying down on the beach.We spent 12 nights in October half term, with our two children aged 6 and 4, and had a very good relaxing family holiday. We spent most of our time lazing around the pool, eating and drinking ourselves stupid at the hotel's bbq buffet, and meeting other likeminded parents, that recognised a good value half term break when they saw one! We also made the most of the hotel's complementary shuttle to its sister hotels down on the beach. Of course, this only happened when we could drag ourselves away from the comfort of the pool. Made even more comfortable with a constant life guard on patrol.On the whole, this hotel is probably more suited to the business short trip traveller. It is certainly more set up for business users. However, don't let this put you off, it is a good quality 5 star hotel, with a (expensive) spa and around 10 bars and restaurants on sight. It also has a complementary shuttle bus to all of the shopping malls, running each morning and evening.	
