Jun 18 2005	convienient	There are 8 hotels in Dubai with the name Le Meridien in them, so be careful which one you book. We booked this through Emirates who we flew with for the purposes of a 2 day stop over. There seems to be a 5 star section and a 31/2 star section - where we stayed. We were dropped off at a difference entrance and served by staff dressed in Emirates Air clothing. The rooms are spacious and air conditioned, which you need in Dubai! Breakfast was good. Pool is good. The gym is excellent, but can get very busy at night - I think it is available to outside members and staff. There is a good selcetin of restaurants a short walk behind the hotel complex. There is a nice little coffe shop in the main entrance area. They have a free bus into the main souk area once a day and one to the beaches area once a day - you can get of here then catch a taxi ( about 8 Dirim) down to Wild Wadi Waterpark. You need to catch a taxi back to the hotel about 30 dirim. Make sure your taxi has a meter BEFORE you get in it - try to use only the white ones with the blue/red stripes or the caramel coloured ones. Taxis can be hard to get at some times in the day, usually early afternoon - 2-3pm.If you need any info or to book any tours etc go to the Business Centre tucked away in a corner of the main reception area of the hotel, they are very helpful. If you want to have afternoon tea at the Burj, BOOK BEFORE YOU LEAVE HOME WEEKS IN ADVANCE AND MAKE SURE YOU ASK TO BE ON THE 27th FLOOR.	
